CLOSEPassengers stepping off their flights at Phoenix Sky Harbor International Airport are being greeted by new signs propped around the concourse.
Doug Ducey's executive order requiring people arriving from the New York City area to immediately self-quarantine for 14 days or face a $2,500 fine.
Before Ducey's order was announced, American and Southwest airlines already had been sending emails reminding passengers to check travel restrictions and quarantines at their destinations.
Other states with travel restrictionsArizona joins other states issuing travel quarantines, all with different approaches to enforcing them.
American, Delta, United and Frontier all have suspended flights between New York City airports and Sky Harbor.